            <bug_when>2009-10-02 18:20:42 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>In addition to the qxh-Locator, it would be nice to have a way of locating qooxdoo widgets through arbitrary JavaScript code. A code snippet that returns a qooxdoo widget could be passed in as the locator string, and the qooxdoo user extension for Selenium would evaluate it (by running eval in the AUT window&#39;s context). Like in the qxh locator, the widget&#39;s DOM element would be returned for Selenium commands to work with.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
